<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1642,1781]" pageId="1" pageNumber="50">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,276,1642,1668]" pageId="1" pageNumber="50">Remarks.</emphasis>
None of the species re-described here fits in the current definition of 
<taxonomicName box="[1146,1277,1643,1668]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Diaphorus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="50" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1146,1277,1643,1668]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="50">Diaphorus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
proposed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Robinson" box="[151,535,1680,1706]" pageId="1" pageNumber="64" refString="Robinson, H. &amp; Vockeroth, J. R. (1981) Dolichopodidae. In: McAlpine, J. F., Peterson, B. V., Shewell, G. E., Teskey, H. J., Vockeroth, J. R. &amp; Wood, D. M. (Co-ords.) Manual of Nearctic Diptera, Vol. 1. Agriculture Canada Monograph, 27, pp. 265 - 639." type="journal article" year="1981">
Robinson and Vockeroth (
<number box="[461,525,1680,1706]" pageId="1" pageNumber="50" value="1981.0">1981</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
. Hence, transferring the species treated in this paper to 
<taxonomicName box="[1198,1318,1681,1706]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Chrysotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="50" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1198,1318,1681,1706]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="50">Chrysotus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
improves the present definition of 
<taxonomicName box="[447,574,1718,1743]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Diaphorus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="50" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[447,574,1718,1743]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="50">Diaphorus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(even though this is a temporary taxonomic solution for 
<taxonomicName box="[1261,1382,1718,1743]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Chrysotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="50" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1261,1382,1718,1743]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="50">Chrysotus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; see Discussion below).
</paragraph>
